markangle(Label("$y$",Relative(0.5)),n=1,radius=9,H,G,F);

[/asy]

The sum of the angle measures in a quadrilateral is always $360^\circ$, so we have  \[360=x+x+y+y=x+x+144+144.\]Therefore  \[x+x=360-144-144=72\]degrees, so $x=\boxed{36}$ degrees.

