label("$B$",B,SE);
label("$C$",C,NW);
label("$D$",D,NE);
label("$E$",E,SW);
[/asy]

answer:
Each number appears in two sums, so the sum of the sequence is \[
2(3+5+6+7+9)=60.
\]The middle term of a five-term arithmetic sequence is the mean of its terms, so  $60/5=\boxed{12}$ is the middle term.

